SIMPLE: sovereign
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sovereign
<hw>Sov"er*eign</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>soverain</ets>, <ets>sovereyn</ets>, OF. <ets>soverain</ets>,
<ets>suvrain</ets>, F. <ets>souverain</ets>, LL. <ets>superanus</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>superus</ets> that is above, upper, higher, fr.
<ets>super</ets> above. See <er>Over</er>, <er>Super</er>, and cf.
<er>Soprano</er>. The modern spelling is due to a supposed connection
with <ets>reign</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Supreme or highest in
power; superior to all others; chief; <as>as, our <ex>sovereign</ex>
prince</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Independent of, and unlimited by, any other;
possessing, or entitled to, original authority or jurisdiction; <as>as,
a <ex>sovereign</ex> state; a <ex>sovereign</ex>
discretion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Princely; royal.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Most
<xex>sovereign</xex> name.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At Babylon was his <qex>sovereign</qex> see.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Predominant; greatest; utmost; paramount.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We acknowledge him [God] our <qex>sovereign</qex> good.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Efficacious in the highest degree; effectual;
controlling; <as>as, a <ex>sovereign</ex> remedy</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such a <qex>sovereign</qex> influence has this passion upon the
regulation of the lives and actions of men.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sovereign state</b></col>, <cd>a state which administers
its own government, and is not dependent upon, or subject to, another
power.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sovereign</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sovereign
<hw>Sov"er*eign</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The person, body, or state in which independent and supreme
authority is vested; especially, in a monarchy, a king, queen, or
emperor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No question is to be made but that the bed of the Mississippi
belongs to the <qex>sovereign</qex>, that is, to the nation.</q>
<rj><qau>Jefferson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A gold coin of Great Britain, on which an effigy of
the head of the reigning king or queen is stamped, valued at one pound
sterling, or about $4.86.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any butterfly of the tribe
<fam>Nymphalidi</fam>, or genus <gen>Basilarchia</gen>, as the ursula
and the viceroy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- King; prince; monarch; potentate;
emperor.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sovereignize</ent>⟦br⟧
